Metro Atlanta

Protesters along Buford Highway condemn ICE arrests

1/24
Pro-immigration protesters march along Buford Highway as they waving flags from Mexico, Cuba, Guatemala and Puerto Rico, and carrying signs condemning deportations, Saturday, February 1, 2025, in Atlanta. About 1,000 protesters on Saturday gathered along Buford Highway, the immigrant hub of metro Atlanta, to call for an end to the targeted operations by immigration agents that began last week. (Hyosub Shin / AJC)
By Ashley Ahn
Updated Feb 2, 2025

About 1,000 protesters on Saturday gathered along Buford Highway, the immigrant hub of metro Atlanta, to call for an end to the targeted operations by immigration agents that began last week.

Waving flags from Mexico, Cuba, Guatemala and Puerto Rico, and carrying signs condemning deportations, hundreds of community members began lining along both sides of the corridor in front of Plaza Fiesta near the DeKalb-Peachtree Airport around noon.
